  {
   "fieldname": "download_section",
   "fieldtype": "Section Break",
   "label": "Download"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "download_info",
   "fieldtype": "HTML",
   "options": "<div class=\"alert alert-info\" style=\"font-size:13px;padding:10px 14px;border-radius:6px\">\n  <strong>How downloads work</strong><br>\n  All file downloads \u2014 public and private \u2014 go through Frappe for permission checks, then redirect the client directly to S3 via a short-lived presigned URL. File content never transits through the Frappe server.\n</div>"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "cors_tab",
   "fieldtype": "Tab Break",
   "label": "CORS"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "cors_info",
   "fieldtype": "HTML",
   "options": "<div class=\"alert alert-warning\" style=\"font-size:13px;padding:10px 14px;border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:12px\">\n  <strong>Cloudflare users</strong> \u2014 if your CDN URL is proxied through Cloudflare, create a <strong>Cache Rule</strong> to bypass the cache for requests whose query string contains <code>X-Amz-Signature</code>. Without this, Cloudflare may serve a cached response with an expired signature to a different client.\n</div>"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "cors_config",
   "fieldtype": "Code",
   "label": "CORS Configuration",
   "options": "JSON"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "migration_tab",
   "fieldtype": "Tab Break",
   "label": "Migration"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "migration_info",
   "fieldtype": "HTML",
   "options": "<div class=\"alert alert-info\" style=\"font-size:13px;padding:10px 14px;border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:12px\">\n  <strong>Migrate existing files</strong><br>\n  Scans all <code>File</code> documents still pointing to local paths (<code>/files/</code> or <code>/private/files/</code>) and uploads them to S3. The job runs in the background \u2014 progress updates every 10 files. Errors are logged per file without interrupting the job.\n</div>"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "migration_status",
   "fieldtype": "Data",
   "label": "Migration Status",
   "read_only": 1
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "rollback_section",
   "fieldtype": "Section Break",
   "label": "Rollback"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "rollback_info",
   "fieldtype": "HTML",
   "options": "<div class=\"alert alert-warning\" style=\"font-size:13px;padding:10px 14px;border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:12px\">\n  <strong>Restore files locally</strong><br>\n  Downloads all files currently on S3 back to your Frappe server and restores their original local paths. Run this before disabling the integration or uninstalling the app to avoid broken links.\n</div>"
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "rollback_status",
   "fieldtype": "Data",
   "label": "Rollback Status",
   "read_only": 1
  },
  {
   "fieldname": "migrate_section",
